Sberbank, Rosneft and RusHydro Advance: Russian Equity Preview

-- B y   M a r i n a   S y s o y e v a
-- 
2011-04-28T20:01:53Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-28/sberbank-rosneft-and-rushydro-advance-russian-equity-preview.html
The following companies may be
active in Russian trading. Stock symbols are in parentheses and
share prices are from the previous close of trading in Moscow.  The 30-stock  Micex Index (INDEXCF)  added 0.3 percent to 1,749.65
yesterday. The dollar-denominated RTS Index rose 0.6 percent to
2,028.94.  OAO Sberbank (SBER RU): OAO Sberbank picked Bank of New
York Mellon Corp. to be its depositary bank as  Russia ’s biggest
lender organizes an American depositary receipts program,
according to a statement e-mailed yesterday. The shares
increased 1.2 percent to $3.66.  OAO Rosneft (ROSN RX): Russia’s largest oil producer
reported first-quarter profit rose 60 percent to $3.88 billion
on higher crude prices. The shares added 1.6 percent to 246.58
rubles.  OAO RusHydro (HYDR LI): Russia’s biggest producer of
renewable energy, said electricity production increased 14
percent in the first quarter from the year-earlier period.
RusHydro added 0.9 percent to $5.195 in  London .  To contact the reporter on this story:
Marina Sysoyeva in Moscow at 
